      <h2>How to Choose Based on Your Trade</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Electrician (Residential):</strong> Werner 5-Ft Fiberglass (4.8). Non-conductive, right height for panels and fixtures, light enough to carry on service calls.</li>
        <li><strong>Electrician (Commercial):</strong> Werner 6308 8-Ft (4.7). You need the extra reach for conduit racks, drop ceilings, and high bay fixtures. Fiberglass is mandatory.</li>
        <li><strong>Drywall / Ceiling Finisher:</strong> Louisville FXP1804HD platform (4.6). The platform eliminates fatigue on 8-hour overhead work days.</li>
        <li><strong>Painter:</strong> Werner 6308 (4.7) for step ladder work. FS1512 extension (5.0) for exterior access. The top tray holds brushes, rollers, and a quart can.</li>
        <li><strong>HVAC Service Tech:</strong> Werner 5-Ft (4.8) for indoor unit access. LANBITOU 14 FT (4.5) for roof-top unit access where multi-position flexibility matters.</li>
        <li><strong>General Contractor / Service Van:</strong> LEVELEVE 22 FT telescoping (4.4). One ladder covers A-frame, extension, and stair configurations. Fits in a short van bed.</li>
        <li><strong>Maintenance Crew:</strong> Louisville FM1404HD twin front (4.6) for confined mechanical rooms. FS1512 extension (5.0) for exterior access.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Final Verdict</h2>
      <p>If you can only buy one ladder for professional contracting, the <strong>Werner 5-Ft Fiberglass Type IA Step Ladder</strong> (4.8 stars) is the answer. It is the most-recommended pro ladder for a reason — correct height for 90% of trade work, non-conductive for electrical safety, and a 300-pound rating that covers every tool belt scenario.</p>
      <p>If you need a taller step ladder, the <strong>Werner 6308</strong> (4.7 stars) scales up to 8 feet without sacrificing stability. For platform comfort during extended overhead work, the <strong>Louisville FXP1804HD</strong> (4.6 stars) is worth every dollar. And for service contractors who need one ladder that replaces three, the <strong>LANBITOU</strong> or <strong>LEVELEVE</strong> multi-position ladders deliver genuine space and time savings on every call.</p>

